  "description": [
    "MORE CANDIDATES REPLY TO COOP QUESTIONNAIRE Six of 20 Democratic candidates for state representative for Yellow stone county replied to the Midland Empire Coop Activities question naire reports R J Thornton Bil lings secretary of the group Prev iously as noted last week 12 of 14 legislative and commissioner candi dates in Carbon county replied to the questionnaire The six candidates were noted hying in accord with the Coop pro gram as follows Charles Banderol Nick Maltese and J E Winsby indicated 100 per cent support for the program Char les F Benson 93 R Stirling Thomp as son 81 and Edwin G Osness 56 Other legislative candidates in cluding those for state senate Frank Gorman D Melvin Hoiness R and Rex Hibbs R did not reply Gorman and Hibbs have no previous legislative records Hoiness in three previous sessions in the house voted with the people as follows 1937 52 1939 17 and 1949 33 Yellowstone house candidates Geb hardt Kreig Pierce and Peters did not reply AH four have rolled very poor records for the people of their county and the state Gebhardts record shows 1939 21 per cent 1941 10 and 00 for the past four sessions"
